---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../lib/jsonld';

const abs = (p: string) => new URL(p, Astro.site).href;
const UPDATED = 'June 1, 2026';
const EMAIL = 'hello@datelore.com';
const jsonld = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'DateLore', url: abs('/') },
    { name: 'Privacy Policy', url: abs('/privacy/') },
  ]),
];
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy · DateLore"
  description="How DateLore handles your data: what we collect, the cookies our advertising and analytics partners use, your choices, and how to contact us."
  ogImage="/og/home.png"
  jsonld={jsonld}
>
  <section class="band band--tight">
    <div class="wrap wrap--narrow stack">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:var(--step-5);line-height:.98;">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="muted">Last updated: {UPDATED}</p>

      <p class="lede">
        DateLore ("we", "us") respects your privacy. This page explains what information is collected
        when you visit <strong>datelore.com</strong>, how it is used, and the choices you have.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">The short version</h2>
      <p>
        DateLore is a static website. There are no accounts and nothing to sign up for. The birthday
        calculator and the daily quiz run entirely in your browser — the dates you enter and your quiz
        streak are stored locally on your own device and are never transmitted to us. The main way
        third-party data is collected is through the advertising and analytics services described below.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Information we collect</h2>
      <ul class="stack" style="padding-left:1.2em;">
        <li>
          <strong>Information you enter:</strong> a birthdate you type into the birthday tool is
          processed in your browser to calculate your stats. It is not sent to or stored by us.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Local storage:</strong> we use your browser's local storage to remember your daily
          quiz streak. This stays on your device and you can clear it at any time through your browser.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Server logs:</strong> like most websites, our hosting provider (Cloudflare)
          automatically records standard technical data such as your IP address, browser type, and the
          pages requested, for security and to keep the site running.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookies and similar technologies:</strong> our advertising and analytics partners
          may set cookies or use similar technologies, as described in the next section.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Advertising</h2>
      <p>
        To keep DateLore free, we display ads served by <strong>Google AdSense</strong> and its
        advertising partners. Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on
        your prior visits to DateLore and other websites, and may use web beacons and similar
        technologies to personalize ads and measure their performance. Google's use of advertising
        cookies is governed by Google's policies; no personally identifying information is provided to
        these partners by us.
      </p>
      <p>
        Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your
        visits. You can learn about and control personalized advertising here:
      </p>
      <ul class="stack" style="padding-left:1.2em;">
        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads &amp; cookies policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener">Google Ads Settings</a> — manage personalized ads on Google</li>
        <li><a href="https://optout.aboutads.info/" rel="noopener">aboutads.info</a> and <a href="https://www.youronlinechoices.com/" rel="noopener">Your Online Choices</a> — industry opt-out tools</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Analytics</h2>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (GA4) to understand how visitors use DateLore — such as
        which pages are popular and how people find us — so we can improve the site. Google Analytics
        sets cookies and collects data including your IP address, device and browser type, and the pages
        you view; this data is processed by Google on our behalf and is not used by us to identify you
        personally. Where consent is required (see below), analytics cookies are only set after you
        agree. You can also opt out with the
        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>,
        and Google describes its handling of this data in its
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" rel="noopener">privacy &amp; terms</a>.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Your consent choices</h2>
      <p>
        If you are visiting from the European Economic Area, the United Kingdom, or another region that
        requires it, you will be asked for consent before non-essential cookies (such as those used for
        advertising and analytics) are set, and you can change or withdraw that consent at any time
        through the on-site consent controls.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have rights to access, correct, or delete personal
        information, or to opt out of the "sale" or "sharing" of personal information for targeted
        advertising under laws such as the GDPR (EU/UK) and the CCPA/CPRA (California). Because we do
        not maintain user accounts, most data is held by the third-party partners listed above — their
        linked policies describe how to exercise these rights with them. You can also contact us using
        the details below.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>
        DateLore is a general-audience site and is not directed to children under 13, and we do not
        knowingly collect personal information from them.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the "last updated" date
        above. Significant changes will be reflected on this page.
      </p>

      <h2 style="margin-top:var(--s5);">Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email us at
        <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`} style="color:var(--gold-deep);font-weight:600;">{EMAIL}</a>, or
        visit the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
